<HEADLINE>
<P>
CHINA'S LOST GENERATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"China's Lost Generation" is another lesson for us in what our freedoms mean to 
others and how important our way of life has become to the rest of the world. 
</P>
<P>
"Tyranny Begins at Home" (by Harry Shearer), is a well-worded warning that we 
must continually work to keep our freedoms. 
</P>
<P>
Thanks for both, and let me say the magazine has become a must-read for me; it 
is always well-done and thought-provoking. 
</P>
<P>
HELEN SONGER, Van Nuys 
</P>
