<HEADLINE>
<P>
CRITICS' PICKS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Sheila Benson 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Noteworthy films, with mini-reviews by Times critics. 
</P>
<P>
Sidewalk Stories 
</P>
<P>
Channel 28 Wednesday at 9 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
In this magical 1989 movie, film maker Charles Lane had the audacity to make a 
black-and-white silent movie with a brimming heart and an activist's outraged 
passion. Lane casts himself as the film Chaplinesque hero, a bashful, ingenious 
Greenwich Village street portraitist who unexpectedly finds himself in charge 
of an adorable 2-year-old. Sheila Benson 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, (Orange County Edition) "Sidewalk Stories": Charles Lane and Nicole 
Alysia. 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
