<HEADLINE>
<P>
CURRENTS: A GUIDE TO THE BEST OF SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA: RITUALS; 
</P>
<P>
CAFE AU LAIT BREAK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ROBIN TUCKER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COFFEE IS for the morning, gulped quickly to wake us up. 
</P>
<P>
Tea is best for two with talk and tiny sandwiches. Cafe au lait, steaming and 
strong in a thick white bowl that must be nurtured with both hands is the 
perfect solitary pleasure. With it, have the final indulgence -- 
orange-flavored biscotti, one side drenched in deep bittersweet chocolate. 
</P>
<P>
 Old Town Bakery, 166 W. Colorado Blvd., Pasadena; (818) 792-7943. 
</P>
<P>
ROBIN TUCKER 
</P>
</TEXT>
