<P>
RENT CONTROL LETTER DRAWS A REBUTTAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mr. Keith Lambert (Letters, April 22) seems to have his concepts of democracy 
and communism a bit askew. 
</P>
<P>
The majority (i.e. tenants) in Santa Monica voted for the rent control law. 
They were free elections, which I consider to be one of the tenets of 
democracy. What Mr. Lambert seems to want is oppression by the minority (i.e. 
landlords) in Santa Monica, similar to what has taken place in the communist 
world. 
</P>
<P>
The majority of the people in Santa Monica voted not only for the Rent Control 
Board but for the City Council that in turn carries out the wishes of the 
people. Where have you been, Comrade Lambert? 
</P>
<P>
NAN LEWIS 
</P>
<P>
Santa Monica 
</P>
