<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: THOUSAND OAKS; 
</P>
<P>
MAN, 29, CHARGED IN ROBBERY, ASSAULT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 29-year-old Thousand Oaks man who allegedly robbed a pedestrian and then 
tried to rob a motorist was arrested Saturday morning, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Ali Razavi, 31, of Thousand Oaks was walking in the 600 block of Westlake 
Boulevard at 7:12 a.m. when he was pushed from behind by the suspect, Arthur 
Kirk Stearns, said Ventura County Sheriff's Lt. Richard Diaz. 
</P>
<P>
Razavi turned around and Stearns demanded money, threatening the victim with a 
chunk of asphalt in one hand, Diaz said. 
</P>
<P>
After Razavi refused, he was punched in the face by the suspect, Diaz said. 
Razavi then gave Stearns the contents of the wallet, about $400, Diaz said. 
</P>
<P>
Stearns ran across Westlake Boulevard and flagged down a motorist, Diaz said. 
After getting into the car, Stearns allegedly tried to rob the driver, who did 
not have any money, Diaz said. 
</P>
<P>
Stearns then got out of the car at Triunfo Canyon Road and Westlake Boulevard 
and was seen by a passing deputy, Diaz said. 
</P>
<P>
The deputy, who recognized Stearns from a description given by Razavi when he 
reported the robbery, chased Stearns on foot, Diaz said. After a short chase 
through several back yards, Stearns was arrested. He is being held at County 
Jail, Diaz said. Bail is set at $30,500. PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
</TEXT>
