launch pad at Cape Canaveral.; Photo, A French Ariane rocket carrying a 
telecommunications satellite lifts off last October. Associated Press; Photo, A 
McDonnell Douglas Delta II hoists a payload for the U.K. on its first 
commercial launch last August. U.S. Air Force; Photo, General Dynamic's Atlas 
Centaur is the smallest launch vehicle of the three U.S. rocket makers in terms 
of the payload it can carry. General Dynamics 
</P>
