<HEADLINE>
<P>
WE NEED BETTER CARS, NOT BETTER CAR ADS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
It seems to me that it would be more pertinent for General Motors to spend $500 
million on improving the quality of GM products than on advertising with NBC 
("GM, NBC Sign Big, Long-Term Advertising Pact," May 1). Doing so could 
increase employment in the industry and increase their sales automatically. 
</P>
<P>
We really don't need more advertising gimmicks but rather better U.S.-made 
automobiles. 
</P>
<P>
J. AHO 
</P>
<P>
La Canada Flintridge 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA051390-0167 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 218413 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
May 13, 1990, Sunday, Home Edition 
</P>
