<HEADLINE>
<P>
NO EASY ANSWERS TO ENVIRONMENTAL ISSUES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
It is refreshing to read a discussion of technology versus ecological 
consciousness/correctness that acknowledges the give-and-take nature of 
humanity's relationship with the Earth ("Cyberpunk and the Future of 
Technology," April 19). 
</P>
<P>
I'm tired of the knee-jerk extremists in both technology and ecology who refuse 
to find a level on which to relate and successfully carry out their plans. 
</P>
<P>
I hope indeed that all of the hype surrounding Earth Day does not simply 
vaporize. It would be symptomatic of what Michael Schrage calls the "disgusting 
attitude" so prevalent in the United States regarding environmental issues. 
</P>
<P>
JEANNE G. WYSHAK 
</P>
<P>
Beverly Hills 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Earth 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
