Slaying of woman -- In Thursday's Westside edition, a word was inadvertently 
dropped from a story about the death of an elderly woman. The sentence should 
have read: Geon, 23, allegedly told police the slaying was provoked when his 
grandmother, 73-year-old Angelica Emma Oser, attacked him and made racial and 
other remarks about his girlfriend, who is black. 
</P>
