<HEADLINE>
<P>
RERUNS TO RE-WATCH: WHEN LUCY GOT TOP MARX 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOAN FANTAZIA, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Star-struck Lucy meets Rock Hudson, Cornel Wilde and Bob Hope this week, but 
it's her encounter with Harpo Marx that leaves her speechless, in a classic 
scene on "I Love Lucy" (Friday at 9:30 a.m. on KTTV). 
</P>
<P>
Lucy gets herself into a jam-but then when doesn't she?-by bragging to her 
friends that while the Ricardos and Mertzes are in Hollywood, they've been 
palling around with the stars. 
</P>
<P>
When one of those friends comes to town, forcing her to put up or shut up, Lucy 
comes up with one of her craziest ideas ever-impersonating such actors as Gary 
Cooper, Jimmy Durante and Clark Gable. And for once, her stunt works. But just 
as she's ready to go on as Harpo Marx, the real Harpo shows up. After he plays 
"Take Me Out to the Ballgame" on his signature instrument, he and Lucy team up 
to do the now-famous mirror routine. 
</P>
<P>
Also during the Ricardo's Hollywood visit, Lucy also gets mixed up with Cornel 
Wilde (Wednesday at 9:30 a.m.), and Rock Hudson shows up on a Palm Springs 
getaway (Thursday at 9:30 a.m. on KTTV). 
</P>
<P>
On a much later episode, when the Ricardos and Mertzes are back home in New 
York, Lucy meets up with Bob Hope (Tuesday at 11 p.m. on KTTV). 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, One of the most popular "I Love Lucy" episodes brought Lucille Ball and 
Harpo Marx face to face. VIACOM ENTERPRISES 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
