<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORE MOVIES: THE WEEK'S OTHER PRIME-TIME FILMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KEVIN THOMAS, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Lina Wertmuller's witty, bittersweet Swept Away (KCET, Saturday at 10 p.m.) 
finds Mariangela Melato's self-absorbed rich woman stranded on an island with 
Giancarlo Giannini's Communist seaman. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, "Batteries Not Included" (KTLA, Monday at 8 p.m., Saturday at 6 p.m.) is 
a delightful 1987 fantasy in which Hume Cronyn and Jessica Tandy star as an 
elderly couple trying to hold out in their now desolate block in Manhattan. 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
