<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
OCC EDGES GOLDEN WEST IN SOFTBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Orange Coast College, aided by two errors and a walk, scored in the first 
inning for a 1-0 victory over Golden West in a Southern California Regional 
softball playoff game Saturday at OCC. 
</P>
<P>
Kristin Heizer pitched a one-hitter to get the victory for OCC (33-11). 
</P>
<P>
Golden West's only hit was a single in the fourth by Sheri Williams. 
</P>
<P>
Pam Fogg pitched a three-hitter for Golden West. The teams play today at noon 
in the second of their best-of-three series at OCC. Should Golden West win, 
another game will follow. 
</P>
<P>
In another regional: 
</P>
<P>
Cypress 8, Grossmont 2 -- Shortstop Tricia Barr had three hits and three runs 
batted in to pace host Cypress. Laura Corson (20-2) pitched a two-hitter for 
the Chargers (39-6). The teams play again at noon today at Cypress, and 
Grossmont (21-15) needs to win to extend the best-of-three series to a third 
game. 
</P>
<P>
In the Southern California men's tennis championships at College of the Desert: 
</P>
<P>
Scott Hansen, an unseeded singles player from Saddleback, pulled off two upsets 
to advance to the semifinals. Hansen defeated No. 3 Tim Clark of Bakersfield, 
6-1, 6-4, and No. 8 Nick Zinzmeister of Desert, 6-2, 4-6, 2-2 retired. 
</P>
<P>
In the semifinals, Hansen will play top-seeded John Swaino of Cypress and Carl 
Hinds of Saddleback, who defeated Derek Hall of Moorpark, 6-0, 6-0, and Jon 
Imel of Long Beach, 6-3, 6-2, will play No. 2 Jon Fox of Santa Barbara. 
</P>
</TEXT>
