<HEADLINE>
<P>
O.C. EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
American Health Services Corp.: The Newport Beach-based operator of outpatient 
diagnostic imaging centers reported first-quarter net income of $325,508, up 
from $106,666 for the like period in 1989. Revenue rose 30% to $7.4 million 
from $5.7 million. S. Lewis Meyer, chairman and president, attributed the 
results to increased operating performance in the company's existing imaging 
centers and profitable operations at three new centers. 
</P>
